# Defense in depth against the 2026-04-19 incident: a Windows component
# in the cursor-agent child process tree (Software Licensing Service /
# ETW / .NET CLR / Defender) called ExpandEnvironmentStrings on a
# hardcoded path like "%SystemDrive%\ProgramData\..." against an env
# block missing SYSTEMDRIVE, got the literal "%SystemDrive%\..." string
# back, and CreateFile resolved it as a relative path under the child's
# cwd (the repo root). The root cause is fixed in
# pkgs/agents/runner/cursor/config.go::defaultPassthroughEnvKeys, but
# this pattern keeps `git status` clean even if a future Windows
# subsystem caches via an env var we forgot to forward.
%*%/
